<subSubSection pageId="200" pageNumber="804" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="200.[2055,2648,2075,2498]" pageId="200" pageNumber="804">
Taxonomy. 
<taxonomicName authority="Carleton &amp; Stanley, 2005" authorityName="Carleton &amp; Stanley" authorityYear="2005" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Hylomyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="200" pageNumber="804" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arcimontensis">Hylomyscus arcimontensis Carleton &amp; Stanley, 2005</taxonomicName>
, Monga Tea Estate, 4-5 km WNW Amani, E Usambara Mountains, Muheza District, Tanga Region, Tanzania.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="200" pageNumber="804" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="200.[2055,2648,2075,2498]" pageId="200" pageNumber="804">
<taxonomicName box="[2057,2204,2272,2301]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Hylomyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="200" pageNumber="804" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hylomyscus</taxonomicName>
arcimontensis was originally included in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[2248,2401,2311,2340]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Praomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="200" pageNumber="804" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="denniae">H. denniae</taxonomicName>
but elevated to species status based on morphological grounds. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="200" pageNumber="804" type="multiple">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="804" startId="200.[2055,2227,2429,2458]" targetBox="[1442,2031,2080,2492]" targetPageId="200">
<paragraph blockId="200.[2055,2648,2075,2498]" lastBlockId="200.[1440,2647,2503,3088]" pageId="200" pageNumber="804">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2055,2231,2429,2458]" pageId="200" pageNumber="804">Distribution.</emphasis>
Eastern Arc Mts from South Pare Mts S to Mt Rungwe, Tanzania, and probably in Misuku Mts in N Malawi.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="200" pageNumber="804" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="200.[1440,2647,2503,3088]" pageId="200" pageNumber="804">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1443,1691,2543,2577]" pageId="200" pageNumber="804">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 75-105 mm,tail 127-137 mm, ear 16-21 mm, hindfoot 18-22 mm; weight 13-5-28-5 g. Fur of the Eastern Arc Wood Mouseis soft and dense, dark brown above and sharply demarcated grayish white below, similar in color to the Montane Wood Mouse (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[1791,1942,2661,2695]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Praomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="200" pageNumber="804" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="denniae">H. denniae</taxonomicName>
). Tail is very long (c.140% of head-body length), dusky brown and appearing naked but with tuft of hair at tip. Ears and eyes are large relative to head. Fifth digit on hindfoot is opposable and almost as long as second to fourth digits. Females have three pairs of nipples. Incisors are orthodont.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
